		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top" id="forumSubject">Halflings make the best druids!<br clear="all" /><script type="text/javascript">document.title = document.title + ": Thread: Halflings make the best druids!";</script>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Mon, Dec 4th 6:52 PM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=8&mid=97595596228343&post=1"><a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=8&mid=97595596228343&num=6&page=0&post=1&replyto=97595596228343"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=97595596228343></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I don't understand why wood elfs seem to be the more popular choice for druids.&nbsp;&nbsp;Let's look at the stats of the halfling vs the woof elf<br><br>Strength: +5 for halfling<br>  This isn't a big deal as far as melee combat goes, but strength is very nice to have for carrying capacity.  I always wish I had higher strength so I could carry more loot.  +5 strength is nice.<br><br>Stamina: +10 for halfling<br>  I don't even need to say much about that, +10 stamina is obviously more hit points and that is a very desirable thing<br><br>Agility: identical<br><br>Dexterity: +10 halfling<br>  Not a big deal but it sure doesn't hurt.  People say you get interrupted when casting less with higher dex, I'm not sure if that's the case or not for sure though.  And special weapons proc more with higher dex.  Like I said no biggie but it helps.<br><br>Wisdom: identical<br><br>Intelligence: +8 woodie<br>  Who cares.  Druids are wis casters.  Your trade skills will go up slightly faster as a wood elf.  Big whoop.<br><br>Charisma: +25 wood elf<br>  This is where all those stat points get dumped.  Charisma.  Pretty useless..the only spell it really effects is the charm animals line which suck no matter which race you are.  And in some situations you will get more money in shops with a higher charisma, but again, that's not really comparable to better strength, dex, and stam.<br><br>Beyond the stats, the halflings start in arguably the best newbie area in the game.  The harder section is walled off, and the zone can hold you up until level 12 or so if you wanted.  And at that point the beholder's maze is a place you can go to next, and it's always pretty empty.  Plus, halflings gain levels faster then wood elfs, with that 5% bonus.<br><br>One thing people who prefer woodies say is 'yeah but halflings look stupid'.  First of all that's a subjective matter, and most of us don't put how we look above how we perform.  Second of all, wood elf druids don't exactly reak of variety either.<br><br>I just felt like opening up this common topic again so see what people thought.  Damn the servers for being down :P<br><br>-- random halfling druid :P</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >6 Replies</td></tr></table>
